shared_text:
FJSHS Athletics/Activities
September 9 at 12:07 PM ·

***NO ADJUSTMENT TO THE FALL SCHEDULE***
In spite of any rumors or incorrectly passed information from outside sources, the CHSAA BOD voted unanimously NOT to change the sports schedule. This means that all sports, football included, remain where they are for this school year. That statement from CHSAA is below.

At a meeting on Tuesday night, the Board of Directors of the Colorado High School Activities Association, addressed a potential change to the 2020-21 sports and activities calendar.

The COVID-19 pandemic has presented many challenges. Specific to CHSAA activities, this has included trying to resume a traditional fall season for moderate- to high-risk contact sports. It has forced inequities when making statewide decisions for the 180,000 student-participants, 363 voluntary members schools, and 178 school districts across the state.

In a resolution Tuesday, the Board of Directors unanimously voted to not reconsider any adjustment to the 2020-21 sports calendar, which was approved on Aug. 4.

August 10 at 9:42 AM ·

The first day of preschool is fast approaching!!!
The first day is scheduled for August 24th, 2020
If you are still needing to turn in paperwork, OR if you still need to meet to get required paperwork picked up to fill out, please contact Misty Hinkle at….
719-784-2516 or mhinkle@re-2.org.

“Small Group” Open House will be scheduled for August 20th. During open house, you will get to meet your teachers and see the classroom. Teachers will go over drop off and pick up procedures, as well as any other information regarding your child’s day at preschool. Teachers will begin contacting all families next week to get schedule a time to come in.

We are ALL very excited to see all of you. We have sure missed being with our students!!!

National Convention Day 4!

shared_text:
Florence FFA Chapter
October 29, 2019 at 9:00 PM ·

Another fantastic day at National Convention!

We started our day bright and early at Crossroads Genetics which is boar stud. They have over 50 boars on site and have sired many of the nations best show hogs!

After we headed into to Indy to get checked in and explore the convention center a little bit! We saw FFA EVERYWHERE!!

We ended our day with a tour of the Indy Scream Park which is home to 5 different haunts and corn production. We got to see the facility behind the scenes and understand how they run this successful operation. Then for a little thrill we can back that night and dared to adventure in all the terrifying attractions!

We are excited to be in Indy and can’t wait for Convention to start tomorrow!!

shared_text:
Florence FFA Chapter
October 28, 2019 at 10:42 AM ·

No snow day for the FFA, we had a great tour this morning at Shatto Milk Company!

Shatto Milk Company is a small family-owned and operated dairy farm located just north of the Kansas City metropolitan area. The family has been farming here for more than 100 years and began a dairy farm more than 80 years ago. They currently have 254 cows that they milk three times a day. Shatto produced lots of specialty products include flavored milk, which ranges from banana to cotton candy and is sold in glass bottle only. They also have ice cream, cheese and butter. Our students had the opportunity to tour the facility, taste product and even milk a cow!

#huskynation #florenceffa #learnbydoing

shared_text:
Florence Howling Husky Pride
October 16, 2019 at 8:58 PM ·

The Howling Husky Pride has won the southern region for the first time in school history! The band scored a 60.75 and is 11 points ahead of where they were this time last year!

We have 61 of the hardest working kids around and we could not be more proud of them! Congratulations on winning the south Howling Huskies! Tomorrow we will find out our place in state! We could not be more proud of you guys!

Keep up the good work and finish strong!

#pianoman #HuskyPride #prooveit #southernregionalchamps #howlinghuskypride

shared_text:
Florence FFA Chapter
October 16, 2019 at 4:07 PM ·

We had a busy day in the Ag department today!

Two of our first year members competed in a regional creed speaking competition in Lamar! Both represented our chapter well and are well on there way to being prepared for district competition in the spring.

We also had a variety of arrangements go out today to celebrate and thank the wonderful administrators we have in our district.
Happy National Administrators month and Bosses Day!

post_text: Awesome job! Congratulations!
shared_text:
Florence Howling Husky Pride
October 13, 2019 at 9:06 AM ·

Yesterday, The Florence High School Howling Husky Pride traveled to the Harrison Marching Festival. They were crowned the 1A champions of this competition. Our students work very hard and are 6 points ahead of where they were this time last year.

As a result of winning class 1A, they performed in a open class finals performance last night and represented very well! The band is making noise across the state!

Congratulations on winning class 1A yesterday band! We are super proud of you guys! Get some well deserved rest and come back ready to hit the ground running on Monday. Regionals is on Wednesday!

#prooveit #pianoman #hardworkpayingoff #howlinghuskypride #huskynation
